public final class ConcurrentNonBlockingThreadPoolExecutor
extends java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor

A ThreadPoolExecutor creates threads before queueing tasks. In Java SE 6, this type of ThreadPoolExecutor can be created with ThreadPoolExecutor#allowCoreThreadTimeOut(boolean)).
